<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">MAKE PEOPLE LOVE YOU</b></font> - <small>Sowrlemn, The Nameless</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    First, most of you enchanters have probably noticed that it gets difficult to find a group once you're at lv 21 or so. This is because we have a very old DD (but that doesn't matter because you shouldn't use it anyways) and, most people only recognize us enchanters as clarity machines or jewel crafters. <p>

This is completely bogus. First off, don't even mem your nuke. Regardless of who is in your group, you should never have any problems, and no one should EVER die. <p>

I've found that one of the fastest ways to level is to get a group with one tank, and the rest wizzies or mages. Again, I will say DO NOT MEM YOUR NUKE. It is too tempting to lob our new DD at the mobs, but trust me: our mana is MUCH better spent mezzing, mass mezzing, and MEM BLURRING. Not many people know how to use this spell effectively, but I garauntee that no one in your party will EVER die if you master just those two or three spells. If someone gets low on health, tell them to stop attacking, and to take a couple steps back. Throw in a mem blur. He'll forget about whoever has low HP. Many young enchanters don't know how mem blur works... Yes, it is true that mem blur is the KS spell of the century. But if you use it this way, you're an idiot, and should be stripped of the ability to use this spell. Mem blur simply erases the hate list of whatever you're attacking... So, if you are fighting gnolls (my favorites at this lv) and a gnoll aggros on a caster, throw in a mem blur, and the gnoll forgets all previous damage done to it. So it's like it thinks the caster hasn't casted yet. And, hopefully your tank is on the ball, and he's hit it since you casted. So, the gnoll will then aggro on the tank. If the entire party starts getting low on health, tell them (and be sure to keep them paying attention to you, as communication is EXTREMELY important when you are mezzing) to all stop attacking, and just stand. throw in a mez, and everyone can just sit there and med and heal. In about 15 seconds, the mob may start to wake, so you tell everyone to stay sitting, and when he aggros, throw in another mez. <p>

With this strategy, you can take out mobs VERY fast. An entire group of casters can take out gnolls in no time. And, no single person is ever in danger, because you have mastered the art of mem blurring. <p>

So, as a recap, remember that you tell your party of the "enchanter tactics" before you pull your first kill... The tank pulls, everyone targets him, and uses assist. You use your mass mez spell, and the tank whacks one, and the rest sleep. No one can use AoE spells, or DoT's (sorry druids) when doing multiple pulls. And, remember that your mana is key to the functioning of the group. Do not EVER go below 20% unless you're doing emergency stuns of mez's. Our job is just to keep things organized, and take targets out one at a time. If the group is in danger, do NOT let them spread out, as you will not be able to mez anything. Just stay close, and be sure to keep up comminication. <P>
<P>
Sowrlemn of Victis Honor, <p>
26 Enchanter (the best class on Norrath!) <P>
p.s. <p>
The thing about making people love you: that just means that by keeping groups alive, and NEVER having to zone or lose kills, people will love you, and appreciate the power of an enchanter. Most people don't think the enchanter has a life before lv 29, but with our mass mez's and mem blurs, we are in fact one of the most powerful classes. The skill of the enchanter can make or break a team. Learn these tactics well, and EVERYONE will love grouping with you. ;) Good luck!
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
